From: qq00qq00 <qq00qq00@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 22:38:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat(relearn):=20F7=20fuel-cut=20blip=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20auto=20clutch+throttle,=20vJoy=20+=20HUD=20status?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

F7 relearn becomes a full relearn: besides gear ratios and the power curve it
also clears the learned rev limiter, then (when parked) auto-engages the clutch
and floors the throttle to free-rev the engine to its fuel cut so the rev
limiter relearns on the spot. Fixes cars stuck in "learning…" forever because
rpm_pct was normalised against the nominal EngineMaxRpm instead of the real cut.

- config: throttle_key (default w), feat_relearn_blip, relearn_blip_timeout_ms
- output: relearn_blip_supported/begin/end on the interface; keyboard holds
  clutch+throttle; vJoy holds keyboard throttle + (vJoy or keyboard) clutch
- tcu: full clear incl. rev limiter; blip runs OFF the data lock so observe()
  keeps learning; shift output suppressed during the blip; stationary/race-on
  gate; aborts if the car moves (Automatic transmission)
- status: transient relearn_status (+rpm) in telemetry, surfaced on the HUD
  pill, ModeSidebar and SettingsOverview
- ui: throttle-key field + F7 note in Advanced settings; en/zh strings
